  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling funds in their professional capacity as an accountant. However, several mitigating factors warrant a lenient sentence on the lower end of the typical spectrum: the defendant has no prior criminal record, the amount is relatively modest ($25,000), and they have demonstrated remorse and a commitment to restitution by partially paying back the stolen funds prior to sentencing. A period of 4 months of incarceration, followed by supervised release and a strict restitution schedule, serves as an adequate deterrent while acknowledging the mitigating circumstances.",
